ps to help you reach that desired word count. We simply can=E2=80=99t get e=
nough of word count and you should too. Here=E2=80=99s a look at what you c=
an expect when browsing our archives. And hopefully, this will help you get=
 as excited about word count as we do.</span></p><h3><strong>Typical Word C=
ount For Different Types Of Texts</strong></h3><p><span style=3D"font-weigh=
t: 400;">In the literary world, there are different ways to write a story. =
And with that, there are different lengths as well. You=E2=80=99ve probably=
 heard of short stories and novels, and perhaps all that is in between. But=
 have you ever asked yourself what counts as short in a short story? Or may=
be you=E2=80=99ve wondered how long a story can go before you can call it a=
 novel? Are there rules that bind what is and what is not in terms of word =
count? And if so, what are these?</span></p><p><span style=3D"font-weight: =
400;">Well, no, there aren=E2=80=99t really word count police who=E2=80=99l=
l shake their head for every excess word. But there is a general range for =
each type of text that writers and scholars alike agree. Take the short sto=
ry, for example. Short stories can have a rough maximum of 7,500 words. Sho=
rt story books range from 3,500 to 7,500 words, but <a href=3D"https://www.=
wordcounttool.com/blog/word-count/how-many-pages-is-1000-words" data-wpel-l=
ink=3D"internal" data-modified-href=3D"https://www.wordcounttool.com/blog/w=
ord-count/how-many-pages-is-1000-words">word count can be as low as 1,000</=
a>. A story more than 7,500 words but less than 17,000, on the other hand, =
is what you call a novelette. This term might be familiar to you, and it is=
 often interchanged with the longer form, novella. Novellas are lengthier t=
han novelettes but usually do not exceed 40,000 words. Stories that do exce=
ed that, however, are =E2=80=93 you guessed it =E2=80=93 novels!&nbsp;</spa=
n></p><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">So, why the need to know all thi=
s? Well, if you=E2=80=99re a writer plotting your story, you have to consid=
er how long you expect your story to be and if it matches with the time you=
=E2=80=99re willing to invest in writing that story. If you want to write s=
omething for short-term, consider writing a short story or novelette, and p=
iece out a concise plotline you can execute in the appropriate amount of wo=
rds.&nbsp;</span></p><h3><strong>Word Count To Pages</strong></h3><p><span =
style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Sometimes professors will ask you to write a re=
port or paper and require a certain number of pages for the length. But how=
