l for your piece, and which ones you can cut out. If, after this, your work=
 is still over the word count, then try rephrasing what you=E2=80=99ve writ=
ten. Shorten long phrases by replacing them with something more concise. Fo=
r example, instead of saying =E2=80=9Cis able to=E2=80=9D you can go for th=
e simpler =E2=80=9Ccan.=E2=80=9D You can also decrease your word count by l=
imiting the use of flowery words. Sometimes, it=E2=80=99s really better to =
be direct, simple, and straight to the point.</span></p><h3><strong>Word Co=
unt For Famous Novels</strong></h3><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Peo=
