l.com/blog/productivity-tools/5-free-services-to-check-for-plagiarism" data=
-wpel-link=3D"internal" data-modified-href=3D"https://www.wordcounttool.com=
/blog/productivity-tools/5-free-services-to-check-for-plagiarism">online pl=
agiarism checkers</a> to ensure your piece is 100% unique and 100% yours.</=
span></p><h3><strong>Final Thoughts For Word Count Tool</strong></h3><p><sp=
an style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Words are everything to a writer. They are o=
ur bread and butter. And although one must not be too caught up with the te=
chnicalities and quantities, it=E2=80=99s still nice to know the numbers be=
hind the masterpiece. Whether it=E2=80=99s a 500-word essay or a 40,000-wor=
